  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Sunkari Tirumala Rao & Ors. versus Penki Aruna Kumari pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_1_902_910','2025INSC92'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SUNKARI TIRUMALA RAO & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>PENKI ARUNA KUMARI </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 1 S.C.R. 902</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 92</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002442025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether a suit for recovery of money filed by partners of an unregistered partnership firm against a partner of the same firm is maintainable. Headnotes&dagger; Partnership Act, 1932 &ndash; Section 69 &ndash; Suit for recovery of money filed by petitioners/plaintiffs, partnership firm, against respondent/defendant, a partner of the same firm &ndash; Trial Court found the suit to be maintainable as partnership business had not commenced &ndash; High Court found suit not maintainable as per Section 69(1) &ndash; SLP against High Court order dismissed<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 17-01-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 30442/2019</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_1_902_910','2025INSC92','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_1_902